gh]]) |after=[[H\u00e9lio Castroneves]] & [[Julianne Hough]]}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Dancing with the Stars (US TV series)|''Dancing with the Stars'' (US)]] quarter-finalist | before=[[Melissa Gilbert]] & [[Maksim Chmerkovskiy]] | years=Season 15 (Fall 2012 with [[Karina Smirnoff]]) |after=[[Ingo Rademacher]] & [[Kym Johnson]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Authority control}}\n<!-- Goes above DEFAULTSORT/Categories -->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ohno, Apolo Anton}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:American autobiographers of Japanese descent]]\n[[Category:American game show hosts]]\n[[Category:American male short track speed skaters]]\n[[Category:American sportspeople of Japanese descent]]\n[[Category:Dancing with the Stars (American TV series) winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2002 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2006 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2010 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic short track speed skaters of the United States]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for the United States in short track speed skating]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for the United States in short track speed skating]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the United States in short track speed skating]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Federal Way, Washington]]\n[[Category:Short track speed skaters at the 2002 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Short track speed skaters at the 2006 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Short track speed skaters at the 2010 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Seattle]]\n[[Category:University of Colorado Colorado Springs alumni]]\n[[Category:American male speed skaters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American short track speed skater}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Infobox speed skater\n| sport       = [[Short track speed skating]]\n| name        = Apolo Ohno\n| image       = ApoloOhno.jpg\n| image_si